            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ To [...] ¶  Forbes, a genial &amp; enlightened cosmopolitan, this modest volume is offered as a small contribution to Melbourne souvenirs by the writer ¶ June 1882 ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.06.00c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To [Archibald] Forbes</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found in Herbarium collections at MEL, without details of the specimen. MS is evidently a draft; it has been folded to make a specimen envelope.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>To [...]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M has left a space for Forbes's given name. The correspondent was almost certainly Archibald Forbes, 'the famous war correspondent', who was on a lecture tour of Australia and who was given a civic dinner by the Mayor of Melbourne on 3 June 1882 at which M was one of the guests (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 5 June 1882, p. 4).</p>
               </note> Forbes, a genial &amp; enlightened cosmopolitan, this modest volume is offered as a small contribution to Melbourne souvenirs by the writer<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The work being presented has not been identified.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">June 1882 </p>
